10. Can Repository Assets Be Reused?

If any answer is NO

STOP

Redesign before introducing AI.

# Rule 02 - Enterprise Domain Driven Design v2
# Part 4 - Domain Governance & Repository Intelligence

# Domain Governance Philosophy

The Domain Model is the heart of the platform.

Every architectural decision must preserve

- Business Meaning
- Domain Integrity
- Aggregate Consistency
- Bounded Context Independence
- Repository Governance

The domain evolves continuously.

Architecture must evolve without becoming inconsistent.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Repository Intelligence

Before creating

Aggregate

Entity

Value Object

Repository

Specification

Policy

Factory

Domain Event

Integration Event

Search the repository.

Questions

Does this already exist?

Can it be extended?

Can it be reused?

Would a duplicate be created?

Never create duplicate domain models.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Aggregate Review

Before creating an Aggregate ask

Is this truly a consistency boundary?

Does it own business rules?

Can invariants be enforced?

Can it remain small?

Does it belong to one Bounded Context?

Can it evolve independently?

If the answer is NO

Redesign the Aggregate.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Aggregate Ownership

Every Aggregate owns

Business Rules

State

Lifecycle

Domain Events

Repository

Persistence

Validation

No Aggregate owns another Aggregate.

Cross Aggregate communication

↓

Events

↓

Saga

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Aggregate Evolution

Aggregates evolve by

Adding behavior

Adding invariants

Publishing new events

Versioning APIs

Never evolve by exposing internal state.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Context Evolution

Bounded Contexts evolve independently.

Changes inside one context

Must not require

Database changes

Repository changes

Entity changes

Inside another context.

Maintain loose coupling.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Domain Evolution

Business rules change.

Model the change.

Never bypass the domain model.

When requirements evolve

Refactor the Aggregate

Not the Controller.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Domain Policies

Policies represent business decisions.

Policies

React to Domain Events.

Examples

LeadQualified

↓

AssignmentPolicy

↓

Assign Sales Agent

CustomerRegistered

↓

WelcomePolicy

↓

Create Onboarding Workflow

Policies remain inside the owning Bounded Context.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Factories

Factories create complex Aggregates.

Factories

Validate

Initialize

Enforce Invariants

Factories never contain business workflows.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Specifications

Specifications represent reusable business rules.

Examples

QualifiedLeadSpecification

EligibleCustomerSpecification

AvailablePropertySpecification

LoanEligibleSpecification

Avoid duplicate validation logic.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Evolution

Every Integration Event

Has

Version

Owner

Schema

Compatibility

Deprecation Strategy

Migration Strategy

Events evolve without breaking consumers.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Published Language

Every Bounded Context exposes

REST DTO

Events

SDK

Documentation

Never expose

Entities

Repositories

Internal Models

Internal Exceptions

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Context Mapping

Relationships

Customer/Supplier

Published Language

Conformist

Partnership

Open Host Service

Anti-Corruption Layer

Choose relationships intentionally.

Never allow accidental coupling.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Governance

Industry Plugins

Own Industry Domains.

Capability Plugins

Own Reusable Capabilities.

Platform Core

Owns Platform Domains.

Never mix ownership.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# AI Governance

AI belongs to AI Context.

AI never owns

Lead

Customer

Workflow

Billing

Media

Business Aggregates validate AI output.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Workflow Governance

Workflow coordinates.

Aggregates decide.

Business Services execute.

Workflow never owns

Business Rules

Repositories

Entities

